<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hicks</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago, Chile</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-22">August 22,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Anxiety over earthquake decreases, although mild shocks still continue;
                            financial and business situation quite serious, and destruction of
                            Valparaiso produces fear of panic; subscriptions raised for relief of
                            sufferers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hicks.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>